a href=\"https://haqtravels.co.uk/win-a-free-umrah/\"><!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph --></a></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	If you win our giveaway, all essentials are covered: flights, hotel, transport, and visa. However, it&rsquo;s good to carry some personal cash for food, shopping, or optional expenses.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a href=\"https://haqtravels.co.uk/win-a-free-umrah/\"><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} --></a></p>\r\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">\r\n	Do you have to be debt-free for Umrah?</h4>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a href=\"https://haqtravels.co.uk/win-a-free-umrah/\"><!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph --></a></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<!-- wp:paragraph --><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph --><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph --><!-- /wp:paragraph --></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a href=\"https://haqtravels.co.uk/win-a-free-umrah/\"><!-- /wp:paragraph --></a></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	According to Islam, it is recommended to clear major debts before going. But if you win this giveaway and your basic needs are met, you may still perform Umrah. It&#39;s best to consult a scholar based on your situation.</p>', NULL, 1, '2025-05-24 13:51:31', '2025-05-26 15:59:28'),
(10, 'How to Apply for Umrah Visa from UK?', 'how-to-apply-for-umrah-visa-from-uk', '1748275267.jpg', NULL, NULL, 'admin', '<p>\r\n	Planning to go for Umrah from the UK? One of the first things you need is a visa. The good news is that you can now apply for an Umrah visa online from the UK. In this simple guide from Haq Travel, we will show you how to apply. You will learn what documents you need, the costs involved, and tips to avoid common mistakes. This guide makes the process easy, no matter if it is your first time or you&#39;re helping someone else.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<b>Understanding the Umrah Visa System in 2025</b></h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	Before you begin your application, it&#39;s important to understand how the visa system works for Umrah in 2025</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>What is an Umrah Visa?</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	An Umrah visa is a special visa that allows Muslims to enter Saudi Arabia to perform Umrah. It is different from a Hajj visa. The Umrah visa is usually valid for 30 days and you must complete your trip within that time.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Types of Umrah Visas for UK Pilgrims</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	There are a few ways you can get an Umrah visa if you live in the UK:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Umrah eVisa: Apply online directly through the Saudi government portal.</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Travel Agency Visa: Apply through a licensed Umrah travel agent like Haq Travel.</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Tourist Visa: You can also use a tourist visa for Umrah if it is allowed at the time of travel.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	Each method has its own steps and costs. Many people choose the online route. it is fast and simple.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<b>Umrah eVisa vs Traditional Application</b></h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	There are two main ways to apply for an Umrah visa, online or through a traditional agent. Here&rsquo;s how they compare.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Benefits of Applying Online</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Getting your Umrah visa online is:</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<b>Fast</b>: It can be approved in 1 to 3 days.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<b>Easy</b>: You can apply from your phone or computer.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<b>Cheaper</b>: You avoid agent fees.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>When to Use an Agent</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	You might want to apply through a trusted travel agent like <b>Haq Travel</b> if:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		You are going in a group.</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		You&rsquo;re not comfortable using the internet.</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		You want a full package including flights and hotels.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<b>Step-by-Step Process: Apply for Umrah Visa Online from UK</b></h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	Below are the process you can do easily.</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Step 1: Visit the Official Site of Haq Travel</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Go to the official site of Haq Travel: https://haqtravels.co.uk/</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Step 2: Fill Out the Form</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Enter your:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Full name (same as passport)</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Nationality (United Kingdom)</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Passport number and issue/expiry date</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Travel details and purpose of visit (Umrah)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Step 4: Upload Documents&nbsp;</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	You will need to upload:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		A clear passport scan (valid for at least 6 months)</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Passport-size photo (white background)</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Proof of accommodation in Saudi Arabia (hotel booking)</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Return flight ticket</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Health insurance (can be included with visa)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Step 5: Pay the Visa Fee</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Pay using a credit or debit card. Fees are usually between &pound;100-&pound;120 including insurance.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Note from Haq Travel</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The visa cost mentioned here (&pound;100&ndash;&pound;120) is separate from any Umrah package you may book. Our Umrah packages (ranging from &pound;810 to &pound;899 for 7 to 14 nights) include accommodation and travel arrangements, but do not include visa or transfer fees unless explicitly stated. Always check the package details or contact us directly to confirm what&#39;s included.</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	&nbsp;</h2>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Step 6: Wait for Approval</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	You&rsquo;ll get an email once your visa is approved. It usually takes 1 to 3 working days. Print your visa and take it with you when you travel.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<b>Documents Required for Umrah Visa from the UK (2025)</b></h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	Here&rsquo;s what you need:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Valid passport (must be valid for at least 6 months)</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Passport-sized photo (white background)</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Hotel booking confirmation</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Flight booking confirmation</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Travel insurance</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Vaccination certificate (like meningitis or COVID, if needed)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	Women under 45 may need to show proof of travel with a mahram (male guardian), depending on the latest Saudi rules.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<b>Umrah Visa for British Citizens vs Non-UK Passport Holders</b></h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	If you live in the UK but hold a non-British passport, you can still apply online. Just make sure your passport is valid, and your UK residence permit is also valid. Some nationalities have different rules. So, check with Haq Travel or the official Saudi visa portal.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<b>Umrah Visa Fees in 2025 for Online Applications</b></h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	The cost of an Umrah visa from the UK is:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Visa fee: around &pound;80</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Health insurance: around &pound;20 to &pound;40</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Total cost: usually &pound;100 to &pound;120</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	Exchange rates may affect the final amount in pounds. Haq Travel can help with your application. We offer full support to keep the process easy and stress-free.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Still not sure which way is best for you? Check out more guides <a href=\"https://haqtravels.co.uk/blog/how-much-is-umrah-visa-from-uk/\"><b>How Much is Umrah Visa from UK?</b> </a></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<b>Note from Haq Travel:</b></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The visa cost mentioned here (&pound;100&ndash;&pound;120) is separate from any Umrah package you may book. Our Umrah packages (ranging from &pound;810 to &pound;899 for 7 to 14 nights) include accommodation and travel arrangements, but do not include visa or transfer fees unless explicitly stated. Always check the package details or contact us directly to confirm what&#39;s included.</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	&nbsp;</h2>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<b>Common Mistakes to Avoid When Applying</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Using an expired passport</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Uploading blurry photos or documents</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Booking flights before getting the visa</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Not checking your email (visa might go to spam)</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Wrong travel dates</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	Double-check everything before you submit the form to avoid delays.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<b>How Long Does It Take to Get an Umrah Visa Online?</b></h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	In most cases, it takes 1 to 3 business days. But during busy seasons like Ramadan or school holidays, it might take longer. Apply at least 2 weeks before your trip to be safe.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<b>FAQs about Umrah eVisa Application from the UK</b></h2>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Can I apply for an Umrah visa by myself?&nbsp;</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Yes, you can. It is easy to do online if you follow the steps.</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Can I apply for an Umrah visa myself?</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">&nbsp;</span></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Yes, you can apply for an Umrah visa online through the official Saudi eVisa portal. The process is easy. It has just a few steps: create an account, submit documents, and make the payment. However, if you&#39;re unsure or traveling in a group, using a trusted agency like Haq Travel is also a great option.</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Do I need a visa for Umrah from the UK?</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">&nbsp;</span></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	All UK residents must have a valid visa to do Umrah in Saudi Arabia, no matter their nationality. You can apply for an Umrah visa. In some cases, you might use a Saudi tourist visa, depending on the travel rules.</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>How to apply for an Umrah visa from the UK?</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">&nbsp;</span></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	You can apply online at the official eVisa portal, or use a licensed UK travel agency, like Haq Travel. Online applications typically take 1 to 3 days. The total cost, including insurance, is about &pound;100 to &pound;120.</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>How to get a free Umrah visa?</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	While Umrah visas typically have a fee, Haq Travel regularly runs giveaways and lucky draws offering <a href=\"https://haqtravels.co.uk/blog/how-to-get-a-free-umrah-ticket/\"><b>free Umrah visas</b></a> to selected participants. Follow Haq Travel on social media and subscribe to their newsletter for updates on upcoming promotions and how to enter.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<b>Final Checklist Before You Travel for Umrah</b></h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	Make sure you have:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Printed eVisa</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Valid passport</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Flight and hotel booking</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Travel insurance</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Vaccine certificates</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	Keep both digital and printed copies with you.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<b>Final Thoughts: Is Online Umrah Visa the Right Choice for You?</b></h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	Applying for an Umrah visa online from the UK is simple, fast, and often cheaper than going through an agent. But if you need help, <b>Haq Travel</b> is here to guide you every step of the way. We hope this guide made your Umrah visa journey a little easier.</p>', NULL, 1, '2025-05-24 13:53:03', '2025-05-26 16:01:07'),
(11, 'What is Included in an Umrah Package?', 'what-is-included-in-an-umrah-package', '1748275298.jpg', NULL, NULL, 'admin', '<p>\r\n	Planning your Umrah trip? It is important to know what is included in an Umrah package so you can prepare well and choose the right one. No matter if you are going for the first time or have been before, this guide will help you understand what to expect.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	In this article, we will cover what is included in an Umrah package. This includes travel, hotels, religious support, and helpful services.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>What is Umrah and Why is it Performed?</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Umrah is a special journey that Muslims take to the holy city of Makkah. It is not like Hajj, which has fixed dates and is required once in a lifetime. Umrah can be done at any time of the year. It is a peaceful way to get closer to Allah and refresh your faith.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Why Picking the Right Package Matters?</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	There are many Umrah packages out there. Some are cheap and basic, while others offer extra comfort and services. Picking the right one means your trip will be smoother, more spiritual, and less stressful.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>How Umrah is Different from Hajj</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Umrah is shorter and has fewer steps than Hajj. You don&rsquo;t need to go to Mina, Arafat, or Muzdalifah like you do during Hajj. But it is still a deeply meaningful act of worship.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<b>Types of Umrah Packages Available</b></h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	When looking for a package, you&rsquo;ll see a few different options. Let&rsquo;s look at the most common types.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Budget Umrah Packages</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	These are the most affordable packages. They include the basics like visa, flights, hotel, and transport. The hotels may be a bit far from the Haram, and the rooms are often shared.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Standard or Mid-Range Umrah Packages</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	These packages offer better hotels, closer to the Haram, and more comfortable transport. It is a good choice for families or those who want something in between.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Luxury and VIP Umrah Packages</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Luxury packages include top hotels (usually 5-star), private transport, and personal guides. If you want to travel in comfort and peace, this is a great option.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Customized and Group Umrah Packages</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Some people want a package made just for them with their own dates, hotel choices, and services. Group packages, on the other hand, are shared with others and usually include group guides and ziyarat tours.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<b>Core Inclusions in an Umrah Package</b></h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	Now let&rsquo;s look at what is usually included in a standard Umrah package.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Umrah Visa Services</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Every pilgrim needs a visa to enter Saudi Arabia. Most travel agents take care of this for you. It is often included in the package cost. If you are curious about the actual fee, check out our guide on <a href=\"https://haqtravels.co.uk/blog/how-much-is-umrah-visa-from-uk/\"><b>how much an Umrah visa costs</b></a> to understand what you might pay depending on your country and package type.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Flight Bookings (Round-Trip Flights)</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Your round-trip flight to Saudi Arabia is included in almost all packages. Some may give you options to choose your airline or class (economy, business).</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Hotel Accommodation in Makkah and Madinah</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	You&rsquo;ll stay in Makkah for Umrah and often spend time in Madinah as well. Packages include hotel stays in both cities. The quality depends on your package:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Budget hotels: farther from Haram, basic rooms</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Mid-range hotels: better location, more comfort</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Luxury hotels: very close to Haram, high-end services</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Ground Transportation and Transfers</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	This includes buses, vans, or private cars. They will pick you up and drop you off at the airport, your hotel, and between cities. Some packages have air-conditioned buses, while VIP ones may include private cars.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<b>Religious Services and Support</b></h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	Doing Umrah for the first time can be confusing. That&rsquo;s why packages often include help with religious steps.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Assistance with Umrah Rituals</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Most group packages include a guide. They show you how to do the rituals. These include Tawaf, which is circling the Kaaba, Sa&rsquo;i, the walk between Safa and Marwah, and wearing Ihram.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Group Leaders and Scholars</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Many packages include a group leader or religious guide. They help answer questions and explain the religious parts of your journey.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Guided Ziyarah Tours</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	These are visits to important Islamic places in Makkah and Madinah. In Makkah, you may visit Jabal al-Noor or Cave Hira. In Madinah, places like Quba Mosque and Uhud Mountain are common.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<b>Additional Amenities and Optional Add-Ons</b></h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	Some packages offer extra services for more comfort.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Meal Plans</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Some hotels offer meals like breakfast only, or half/full board (2-3 meals a day). This is helpful, especially for families or elderly travelers.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Travel Insurance</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Many travel agencies now offer travel insurance. It can cover medical emergencies, lost luggage, or trip cancellations.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Mobile SIM Cards and Wi-Fi</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Some packages give you a local SIM card so you can stay connected. Others may provide hotel Wi-Fi or portable internet.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Laundry Services and Hotel Extras</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Luxury hotels often include laundry, daily cleaning, and even room service.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Optional Trips to Nearby Cities</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	You may also visit Taif or Jeddah for sightseeing, shopping, or relaxing after your Umrah.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<b>Services That May Not Be Included</b></h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	Not everything is covered in every package. It is good to know what is not included so you can plan ahead.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Personal Shopping and Extra Costs</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Buying gifts, snacks, or prayer items are your own expenses. Always carry some extra money for these.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Medical Tests (If Needed)</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	You might need a PCR test or health check. This depends on your country&#39;s rules or Saudi requirements. This may not be covered.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Visa Issues or Rejections</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	If your visa is delayed or rejected, travel agents may charge fees. Read their terms before booking.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<b>Factors Affecting the Cost of an Umrah Package</b></h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	Many things can change the price of a package.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Season and Time of Year</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Going during Ramadan, school holidays, or Hajj season can make prices go up. If you go during the off-season, it is usually cheaper.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Hotel Class and Location</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Closer hotels to the Haram are more expensive. Staying even 10 minutes away can save you a lot.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Airlines and Flight Options</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Some packages include top airlines with more baggage allowance. Others use budget airlines to save money.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Length of Stay and Number of People</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Longer stays cost more. Traveling with more family members might give you group discounts.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<b>How to Choose the Right Umrah Package</b></h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	Choosing the right package depends on your needs and budget.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Know Your Budget and Needs</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	If you are young and healthy, a budget package might work. If you have elderly parents or young kids, consider more comfort.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Compare Agencies and Reviews</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Look for trusted travel agencies with good reviews. Ask family or friends who have gone before.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Check the Travel Agency&rsquo;s License</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Make sure your agent is approved by the Saudi Ministry of Hajj and Umrah. This helps you avoid scams.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Understand what is Included</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Ask for a full list of services. Don&rsquo;t assume something is included, always double-check.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<b>Summary</b></h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	Umrah is a beautiful spiritual journey. With the right package, your trip can be peaceful, stress-free, and full of blessings. Make sure you choose a package that matches your needs, budget, and comfort level.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Speak with a trusted travel agent. Compare your options. Get ready for one of the most important journeys of your life.</p>', NULL, 1, '2025-05-24 13:53:29', '2025-05-26 16:01:38');
INSERT INTO `blogs` (`blogs_id`, `blogs_name`, `blogs_url`, `blogs_image`, `blogs_tag`, `blogs_date`, `blogs_author`, `blogs_details`, `blogs_sort`, `blogs_status`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(12, 'Best Time to Go for Umrah from the UK', 'best-time-to-go-for-umrah-from-the-uk', '1748275350.jpg', NULL, NULL, 'admin', '<p>\r\n	Planning to go for Umrah from the UK? You are not alone. Every year, thousands of Muslims in the UK prepare for this special journey to Makkah. But one big question always comes up: When is the best time to go for Umrah? In this article, we will look at different seasons. We will discuss their pros and cons. You&rsquo;ll also learn how to pick the best time for your trip.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<b>What is Umrah and How It Differs from Hajj?</b></h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	Umrah is a pilgrimage to Mecca that Muslims can do at any time of the year. It includes a set of rituals like Tawaf (circling the Kaaba) and Sa&rsquo;i (walking between the hills of Safa and Marwah). Umrah is different from Hajj. Hajj happens on set days in Dhul-Hijjah. But Umrah is shorter and not required. Still, it is a highly rewarding and spiritual act of worship.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Growing Popularity of Umrah Among UK Muslims</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	More Muslims from the UK are choosing to perform Umrah every year. It&#39;s easier now with better travel options, direct flights, and online visa applications. Families, students, and older adults all make this journey for peace, forgiveness, and connection with their faith.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<b>Peak vs Off-Peak Umrah Seasons</b></h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	Just like holidays have busy and quiet times, Umrah does too. Peak times mean more people, longer lines, and higher prices. Off-peak times are quieter, cheaper, and easier, especially for first-time visitors.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Key Islamic Months and Their Significance for Umrah</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Ramadan is a very special time for Umrah. Praying in Makkah during this month brings extra rewards. But it&#39;s also the busiest and most expensive time.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Other good months include:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Rabi al-Awwal: The month of the Prophet Muhammad&rsquo;s (PBUH) birth.</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Shawwal: Right after Ramadan. It&rsquo;s less crowded.</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Muharram: The Islamic New Year month, often peaceful and not too busy.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<b>Seasonal Weather in Saudi Arabia: When to Travel</b></h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	The weather in Saudi Arabia is quite different from the UK. So, pick a time that fits your comfort and health. You can apply for an Umrah visa through approved agents or online. If you&rsquo;re unsure about how much it costs, check the updated<a href=\"https://haqtravels.co.uk/blog/how-much-is-umrah-visa-from-uk/\"> <b>Umrah visa cost for the UK</b></a> to plan your budget better.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Winter Months (November to February)</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	This is the best time for most UK pilgrims. The weather is cooler and easier to handle, especially when doing outdoor rituals. Temperatures stay around 20&deg;C to 30&deg;C during the day.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Summer Months (June to August)</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	It gets very hot in Saudi Arabia in the summer. Temperatures can go over 45&deg;C. If you are not used to this kind of heat, it can be difficult. It&rsquo;s important to drink lots of water and avoid the sun when you can.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Spring and Autumn (March&ndash;May, September&ndash;October)</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	These are good months if you want a balance between price, weather, and crowds. The weather is warm but not extreme. These months also offer better deals on hotels and flights.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<b>Cheapest Time to Perform Umrah from the UK</b></h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	Planning your trip during the right months can help you save a lot on flights and hotels.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Flight and Accommodation Price Trends</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Prices go up during UK school holidays, Ramadan, and December holidays. If you are looking to save money, avoid these times.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Flights and hotel rates are lowest during:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Early January (after New Year)</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Mid-February (outside of half-term holidays)</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		After Hajj season ends (around September)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Off-Peak Periods for Lower Costs</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Traveling in off-peak months like Muharram or Safar can help you save money. You&#39;ll also enjoy a more relaxed and peaceful visit. Many travel agencies offer discounts during these times.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<b>Best Time for a Comfortable and Crowd-Free Umrah</b></h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	To enjoy a peaceful experience, steer clear of busy seasons and public holidays.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Avoiding School Holidays and Public Holidays in the UK</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Try to avoid times when schools are closed in the UK. That&rsquo;s when families travel more, and everything gets busier and more expensive. Booking during term time can give you cheaper and quieter options.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Mid-Ramadan and Non-Vacation Months</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	To enjoy the reward of Umrah in Ramadan without the crowds, try going in the middle of the month. Non-vacation months like Rajab or Rabi al-Thani are also peaceful.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<b>Spiritual Rewards of Umrah in Specific Months</b></h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	Some months offer greater spiritual benefits. This makes your journey more meaningful.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Umrah in Ramadan: Virtues and Challenges</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Doing Umrah in Ramadan is a dream for many. The Prophet Muhammad (PBUH) said that performing Umrah in Ramadan is as rewarding as Hajj. However, it is not required like Hajj. The energy, prayers, and unity during this month are amazing.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	But it can be hard too. It&rsquo;s hot, crowded, and tiring. Consider the needs of children or elderly family members before picking this time.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Lesser-Known Sacred Times with High Spiritual Value</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Other months like Dhul-Qa&lsquo;dah or the first ten days of Dhul-Hijjah also bring great rewards. They are less popular than Ramadan, but still full of blessings. These times are great if you want a meaningful experience without too much stress.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<b>School Holidays and Work Leave Considerations for UK Residents</b></h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	If you have a family or job, timing your Umrah with school and work schedules is key to a smooth trip.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Planning Around UK Academic Calendar</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	If you have school-aged children, you&#39;ll need to plan your Umrah during school breaks like:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Half-term (February, May, October)</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Easter break</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Christmas holidays</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	But remember, these are peak times. Everything will cost more, and Makkah will be more crowded.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Using Bank Holidays for Extended Pilgrimage Trips</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	You can also plan your Umrah around UK bank holidays. This way, you can take fewer days off work but still have a longer trip. Just make sure you book early to get the best deals.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<b>Travel Tips and Health Considerations for Umrah Timing</b></h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	No matter when you go, staying healthy and planning smart can make your Umrah easier and safer.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Health Precautions in Summer and Peak Times</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	If you go during summer or Ramadan, it&rsquo;s important to stay safe:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Drink lots of water</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Wear a hat and light clothes</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Take breaks in the shade</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Bring sunscreen and sunglasses</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	Make sure you also check with your GP for travel vaccines and health advice.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Booking Tips for Flights and Hotels Based on Season</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Book early if you plan to travel during busy times. Prices go up fast. If you are flexible with dates, you can find better deals. Also, check out different UK airports. Sometimes, flying from Manchester or Birmingham costs less than flying from London.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<b>Summary: When is the Best Time to Go for Umrah from the UK?</b></h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	Let&rsquo;s wrap up by comparing the best months based on comfort, cost, and spiritual value.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Best Time for Affordability</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Travel during off-peak months like Muharram, Safar, or after Hajj season (around September).</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Best Time for Spiritual Benefits</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Ramadan is the most rewarding month for Umrah, especially the last ten nights. Dhul-Hijjah and Rabi al-Awwal are also good.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Best Time for Comfort and Convenience</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Winter (November to February) is ideal for UK pilgrims. The weather is cooler, and the experience is easier.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Your choice depends on what matters most to you: cost, comfort, or spiritual value. Think about your health, budget, and family needs before booking.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<b>FAQs About Umrah Timing from the UK</b></h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	Here are answers to common questions UK pilgrims have when planning their Umrah.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<b>Can I go for Umrah during UK school holidays?&nbsp;</b></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	A: Yes, but expect higher prices and bigger crowds.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<b>Is it safe to go in the summer?&nbsp;</b></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	A: Yes, but be careful of heat. Stay hydrated and avoid the sun when possible.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<b>What month is best for a quiet Umrah?</b></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<b>&nbsp;</b>Months like Muharram, Safar, and Rajab are usually less crowded.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<b>How far in advance should I book my Umrah trip?</b></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<b>&nbsp;</b>If you are going during peak times, book at least 3-6 months early.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<b>Do I need a visa for Umrah from the UK?&nbsp;</b></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Yes. You can apply for an Umrah visa through approved agents or online.</p>', NULL, 1, '2025-05-24 13:53:54', '2025-05-26 16:02:30'),
(13, 'Umrah for Women: Step-by-Step Guide', 'umrah-for-women-step-by-step-guide', '1748276400.jpg', NULL, NULL, 'admin', '<h2>\r\n	<b>Umrah for Women</b></h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	Learn what Umrah means for women and why this sacred journey holds deep spiritual value.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>What is Umrah?&nbsp;</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Umrah is a short pilgrimage to Makkah. It is a visit full of prayer and peace. Unlike Hajj, you can do Umrah at any time of the year.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Importance of Umrah for Muslim Women</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	For many sisters, Umrah is a dream. It brings the heart closer to Allah, washes away sins, and gives new hope.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Spiritual and Practical Benefits of Performing Umrah</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	You gain stronger faith, patience, and unity. You also learn how to travel with good manners and help others.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<b>Umrah Rules for Women</b></h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	Know the key rules, eligibility, and special requirements for women planning to do Umrah.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Who Can Perform Umrah?&nbsp;</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Muslim and able to pay for the trip.</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Healthy enough to walk the rites or have help.</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Mature girls should get family consent.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Do Women Need a Mahram for Umrah?</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Most scholars say an adult woman should travel with a mahram (father, husband, son, brother). Some allow her to join a safe, trusted group. Check your local fatwa and visa rule before booking.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Umrah Conditions for Women</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Make niyyah (clear intention).</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Have a valid visa and passport.</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Plan for any medical needs.</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Promise to follow all Saudi and Sharia rules.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Ihram Clothes</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	<b>&nbsp;</b>Women wear their regular loose and modest clothing, such as an abaya or long dress. There is no special color or style required, as long as it is modest. Men, on the other hand, must wear two white, unstitched pieces of cloth, one for the upper body and one for the lower body. This is their specific Ihram clothing.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Hair&nbsp;</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	During Umrah, women must keep their heads covered at all times. After completing Umrah, they should cut a small portion of their hair, about the length of a fingertip. Men must keep their heads uncovered while in Ihram. After Umrah, they must either shave their heads, which is more rewarding, or trim their hair short.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Footwear&nbsp;</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Women are allowed to wear any type of shoes that are comfortable, whether open or closed. There are no strict rules about the design. Men, however, must wear sandals that leave the ankles and the top of the foot exposed. Covered shoes are not allowed for men during Ihram.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<b>Step-by-Step Umrah Guide for Women</b></h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	<i>A simple and clear guide showing each step of Umrah for sisters, from Ihram to the final dua.</i></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>What Women Should Know?</b></h3>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Study the rites with a trusted scholar or guide.</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Speak to your doctor if you are pregnant or on medicine.</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Plan prayers for monthly cycle days; you can still make duʿāʾ.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>How to Perform Umrah for Women</b></h3>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Enter Ihram at the miqat. Say the talbiyah: <i>&ldquo;Labbaik Allahumma Labbaik...&rdquo;</i></li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Tawaf: Walk seven times around the Kaaba. Keep your left side toward it.</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Pray two rakʿah near Maqam Ibrahim or anywhere in the Mosque.</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Sa&rsquo;i: Walk seven times between Safa and Marwa hills.</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Cut hair equal to a fingertip&rsquo;s length to exit Ihram.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Ghusl for Umrah Women</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Take a full shower (ghusl) before Ihram if you can. Clean body, trim nails, remove unwanted hair. This is sunnah, not an absolute must if water or time is short.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Tawaf and Sa&rsquo;i Guidelines for Women</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Move at a steady pace; no need to rush.</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Stay with your mahram or group.</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		If crowded, avoid the inner ring for safety.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Do Women Have to Cut Their Hair for Umrah?</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Yes. After Sa&rsquo;i, clip at least a fingertip length (about 2 cm) from the ends of your hair. You can tie hair in a small braid first, then trim the end.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<b>Ihram for Women for Umrah&nbsp;</b></h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	<i>Explore what Ihram means for women, how to enter this sacred state, and what to wear.</i></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>What is Ihram for Women?</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Ihram is a sacred state. You enter it by making an intention at the miqat and wearing proper, modest clothes.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Women&rsquo;s Ihram vs Men&rsquo;s Ihram</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Women keep normal, loose clothing; men wear two pieces of white cloth. Both avoid perfume, hair pulling, and nail cutting during Ihram.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Women&rsquo;s Dress Code for Umrah</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Loose abaya or maxi dress.</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Opaque fabric, light colors for heat.</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Headscarf that covers hair fully.</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		No face veil during tawaf if it touches the face; use a long peaked cap or hold the niqab away if you wear one.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<b>Umrah Clothing for Women</b></h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	<i>Find out how to choose the best clothes for Umrah that are both respectful and comfortable.</i></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Recommended Umrah Dresses for Women</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Light cotton abaya</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Jersey maxi dress with cardigan</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Long tunic and palazzo pants</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Choosing the Right Umrah Abaya for Women</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Look for:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Breathable fabric</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Front zip for quick wudu</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Side pockets for phone or ID</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Best Fabric Choices for Hot Weather and Comfort</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Cotton, rayon-blend, or linen mixes. Avoid thick polyester.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Layering and Color Suggestions for Ihram</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	White, beige, or soft pastels reflect the sun and show unity. Carry a thin shawl for air-conditioned areas.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<b>Shoes and Footwear for Umrah Women</b></h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	<i>Discover the best shoe options for women to walk safely and comfortably during Umrah.</i></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Women&rsquo;s Footwear During Ihram</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Shoes must be clean, comfy, and easy to slip on and off. Closed shoes are allowed for women.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Best Shoes for Umrah Women</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Lightweight trainers with mesh</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Soft leather sandals with arch support</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Cushioned slip-ons for elderly sisters</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	Tip: Break in new shoes at home to avoid blisters.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<b>Umrah Essentials for Women: What to Pack</b></h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	<i>Use this smart packing checklist to ensure you bring everything needed for a smooth Umrah.</i></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Documents &amp; Money</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">&nbsp;</span></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Bring your passport with a valid Umrah visa. You may also need a national ID. Don&#39;t forget a debit or credit card, plus some cash. It&#39;s good to have both your local currency and Saudi Riyals.</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Worship Essentials&nbsp;</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Pack a small Quran for reading, dhikr beads (tasbeeh) for remembrance, and a pocket-sized book of duas or supplications.</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Clothing&nbsp;</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Bring 2 to 3 abayas or loose dresses. They should be comfortable and breathable. Bring at least 2 clean headscarves for each day. Also, pack comfortable undergarments and several pairs of socks.</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Footwear&nbsp;</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Wear comfortable walking shoes or trainers that are already broken in. Also pack a pair of lightweight flip-flops or sandals for the hotel and bathroom use.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Toiletries Use only unscented items while in Ihram. Take a toothbrush, toothpaste, unscented soap or body wash, wet wipes, tissues, nail clippers, and a comb or brush.</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Health &amp; Medical Supplies</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;Pack your prescription medications. Include pain-relief cream or balm for sore muscles. Don&rsquo;t forget basic first aid supplies like band-aids and blister pads for your feet.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Carry hand sanitizer, preferably unscented.</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Tech Essentials</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">&nbsp;</span></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Always have your smartphone, a wall charger, a universal power adapter, and a power bank for on-the-go charging.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Headphones are helpful for listening to the Quran or lectures.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Bags &amp; Storage</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;Use a lightweight cross-body bag to carry essentials when outside. Also take a small backpack for day trips and a zipper pouch to safely store your documents and money.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<b>Tips for Women on Umrah</b></h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	<i>Helpful tips for staying safe, healthy, and respectful during your time in the holy cities.</i></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Staying Safe While Traveling Alone or with Groups</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Share hotel and group contacts with family.</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Keep valuables tucked under the abaya in a thin belt pouch.</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Walk in well-lit areas and avoid late nights alone.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Social and Religious Etiquette During Umrah</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Speak kindly; smile often.</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Give way to older pilgrims.</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Keep your space clean; dispose of trash in bins.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Managing Health, Fatigue, and Personal Needs</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Drink plenty of Zamzam and bottled water.</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Snack on dates, nuts, or fruit between rites.</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Rest in shaded zones; do stretches for legs.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Tips for Elderly Women or First-Time Pilgrims</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Book wheelchair service for long distances.</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Stay in a hotel near the Haram if budget allows.</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Do tawaf on upper floors where crowds are lighter.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	<b>Read more: </b><a href=\"https://haqtravels.co.uk/blog/how-to-perform-umrah-with-elderly-parents/\">How to Perform Umrah with Elderly Parents</a></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<b>FAQs About Umrah for Women</b></h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	<i>Clear answers to the most asked questions from sisters preparing for their pilgrimage.</i></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<strong>Do women have to cut their hair for Umrah?&nbsp;</strong></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Yes, after completing Umrah, women must cut a small portion of their hair, about the length of a fingertip from each end of their hair. It is a required step to complete the Umrah.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<strong>How to perform Umrah for women?&nbsp;</strong></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Women perform Umrah almost the same way as men. The main steps include:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Wearing Ihram from the Miqat (in regular modest clothing)</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Making Niyyah (intention) and saying the Talbiyah</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Tawaf around the Kaaba 7 times</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Praying 2 rak&#39;ahs behind Maqam Ibrahim</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Drinking Zamzam water</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Sa&rsquo;i between Safa and Marwah (7 rounds)</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Cutting the hair to end Umrah</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>\r\n	Women must stay modest, cover their hair, and avoid pushing or mixing with men during rituals.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<strong>Do women need a mahram for Umrah?</strong></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	This depends on the rules of the country you&rsquo;re traveling from. Some scholars say a mahram is required, while others allow women to travel in a trusted group without one. As of now, Saudi Arabia allows women to perform Umrah without a mahram if they are part of an organized group or tour.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>How Much Hair Should Women Cut After Umrah?</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Trim at least a fingertip length from the ends of all hair strands.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<b>Resources for Further Learning</b></h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	<i>Helpful books, videos, and PDFs to learn more about performing Umrah as a woman.</i></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Downloadable Umrah Guide for Women PDF</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Many mosques and travel sites host free, simple PDFs. Search &ldquo;Umrah guide for women PDF&rdquo; and pick one from a trusted Islamic center.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Umrah Guide for Women in Urdu</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	If you prefer Urdu, look for books by Darussalam or local scholars. Video lessons on YouTube also help.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Recommended Books, Blogs, and Scholar Videos</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		<i>&ldquo;How to Perform Umrah Made Easy&rdquo;</i> by Dr. Bilal Philips</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Vlogs by sisters who share packing tips</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Podcasts from Medina University graduates</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<b>Conclusion</b></h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	A last reminder: every woman can do Umrah with confidence, peace, and purpose. With the right knowledge, good company, and pure intention, every woman can finish Umrah with joy and calm.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>', NULL, 1, '2025-05-24 13:54:15', '2025-05-26 16:20:00'),
(15, 'Group Umrah Packages with Flights, Hotels & Ziyarat', 'group-umrah-packages-with-flights-hotels-ziyarat', '1748276873.jpg', NULL, NULL, 'admin', '<p>\r\n	Umrah is a special journey that Muslims make to the holy city of Makkah. It is not the same as Hajj, but it is still very important in Islam. People from all over the world go to Makkah to perform Umrah. One of the best ways to do this is by joining a group Umrah package.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	A group Umrah package means you travel with a group of people who have the same goal as you. It can be your family, friends, or even people you meet for the first time. Traveling in a group makes the trip easier, more affordable, and more enjoyable.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Let&rsquo;s look at group Umrah packages. We&rsquo;ll discuss the types and why they could be the best choice for your next spiritual trip.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<b>Understanding Umrah and Its Spiritual Significance</b></h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	Umrah is a beautiful act of worship. It involves visiting the Kaaba, walking around it, and doing some special prayers. Many Muslims feel a deep connection to Allah during this time. It helps people feel closer to their faith.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Even though Umrah is not required like Hajj, it is highly recommended. It is a chance to wash away past sins and get a fresh start.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>What Are Group Umrah Packages?</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Group Umrah packages are travel deals made for people going on Umrah together. These packages have all you need. They include flights, hotels, transport, and sometimes food too. A guide or group leader helps everyone stay on track and understand what to do.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	These packages are planned by trusted travel agencies. They help you focus on your worship while taking care of the travel details.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Why Choose a Group Package for Umrah?</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Traveling in a group has many benefits. It is usually cheaper because costs are shared. It is also safer and more organized. You do not have to worry about getting lost or missing anything important. Plus, you get to meet new people and share the experience together.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Many people, especially those going for the first time, feel more confident when they are in a group.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<b>Types of Group Umrah Packages Available</b></h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	There are different types of group Umrah packages. You can pick one that fits your needs and budget.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Economy Umrah Packages for Groups</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Economy packages are for people who want to keep costs low. These packages include basic hotels and travel. They cover everything you need but skip luxury services. This is a great option for students, families, or anyone looking to save money.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Deluxe &amp; Premium Group Umrah Packages</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Deluxe packages offer better hotels and more comfort. They are closer to the Haram (holy mosque), which saves time and energy. Premium packages may also include extra services like buffet meals or private buses. These are great for elderly travelers or those who want a more relaxing trip.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Customizable and Private Group Tours</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Some people want to travel only with their close family or friends. Custom packages let you choose your dates, hotels, and other details. These are more flexible but may cost more. You still get all the services but with more control over your trip.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<b>Key Features of Group Umrah Packages</b></h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	Group Umrah packages come with many helpful features. These make your journey smooth and stress-free.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Flights, Accommodation, and Transport</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Most group packages include return flights from your country to Saudi Arabia. You also get hotel stays in both Makkah and Madinah. Transport between cities and to the holy sites is part of the deal.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Hotels are chosen based on how close they are to the mosques. Closer hotels are more expensive, but they save walking time.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Visa Processing and Documentation Support</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Getting a visa can be tricky. Travel agencies that offer group Umrah packages take care of this. They help you collect the needed documents and apply on your behalf. This saves time and reduces the risk of mistakes.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Guided Ziyarat and Tours in Makkah &amp; Madinah</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Ziyarat means visiting special Islamic places. Most group packages offer guided tours to key sites. These include the Cave of Hira, Masjid Quba, and the grave of Prophet Muhammad (PBUH). A guide explains the history and helps you understand their importance.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<b>Benefits of Choosing a Group Umrah Package</b></h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	Group Umrah packages offer many advantages. Let&rsquo;s look at some of the biggest reasons people choose them.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Cost-Effective Travel for Families and Communities</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Traveling with a group can lower the price for each person. Sharing buses, hotels, and guides helps save money. This is especially useful for large families or community groups.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Guided Assistance and Religious Support</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Many group packages include a religious guide or scholar. They help you perform Umrah correctly and answer any questions. This is very helpful if you are going for the first time or want to learn more.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Safety and Companionship During the Pilgrimage</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Being in a group makes travel safer. If someone gets sick or lost, others are there to help. You also get to make new friends and share a spiritual experience together. It brings people closer and creates beautiful memories.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<b>How to Choose the Right Group Umrah Package</b></h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	Choosing the best package depends on your needs. Here are a few things to keep in mind.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Consider Your Budget and Group Size</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Think about how much you can spend and how many people are going. A big group may get special deals. Your budget will help you decide between economy and premium packages.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Check Accommodation and Travel Inclusions</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Look at the hotels included in the package. Are they close to the Haram? Do they offer meals? Make sure transport between cities and to ziyarat spots is also included.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Reputation of the Umrah Tour Operator or Travel Agency</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Always choose a travel agency that is licensed and experienced. Read reviews and ask for references. A good agency makes your journey smooth and safe.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<b>Best Time to Book Group Umrah Packages</b></h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	Knowing when to book can help you save money and avoid crowds.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Seasonal Considerations: Ramadan, Hajj, Off-Peak</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Umrah can be done at any time of the year, but some months are more popular. Ramadan is a special time for Umrah, but it is also the busiest. Off-peak seasons are less crowded and often cheaper.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Early Booking vs Last-Minute Deals</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Booking early gives you more choices and better prices. Some agencies offer last-minute deals, but they may have limited options. It is best to plan early, especially if you are going with a big group.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<b>Popular Destinations in Group Tours</b></h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	Group packages often include visits to holy sites in both Makkah and Madinah.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Historical Islamic Sites in Makkah</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	In Makkah, you can visit Jabal al-Noor. This is where the Prophet (PBUH) got his first revelation. You can also see the Kaaba and other important mosques nearby.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Spiritual Landmarks in Madinah</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	In Madinah, most groups visit Masjid an-Nabawi, the Prophet&rsquo;s Mosque. You may also go to Masjid Quba, the first mosque built in Islam, and Mount Uhud, the site of a famous battle.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<b>Tips for a Comfortable and Rewarding Group Umrah Experience</b></h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	Going to Umrah is a special time. Here are some tips to help make it even better.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Health, Safety, and Packing Tips for Group Travelers</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Make sure you bring comfortable shoes, light clothing, and any medicines you need. Stay hydrated and rest when needed. Traveling with a group means helping each other, so be kind and supportive.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Etiquette and Behavior in Holy Cities</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Makkah and Madinah are holy places. Always speak politely, respect others, and follow the rules. Be patient in crowds and avoid pushing. Remember, you are a guest in Allah&rsquo;s house.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<b>Frequently Asked Questions About Group Umrah Packages</b></h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<b>Can children join group Umrah tours?</b></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Yes, many families travel with children. Just make sure the package is family-friendly.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<b>Do group packages include meals?</b></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Some do and some don&#39;t. Check with the agency before booking.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<b>How long does a group Umrah trip usually last?</b></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;Most trips are 7 to 14 days, depending on the package.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<b>Is it safe to travel in a group during Umrah?</b></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Yes, traveling in a group is often safer than going alone.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<b>Conclusion</b></h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	Group Umrah packages are a smart and helpful way to go on this important journey. They offer comfort, safety, guidance, and great value for money. Going with family, friends, or even strangers can help you feel closer to Allah and to one another.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Picking a good package from a reliable travel agency leads to a calm and easy trip. Plan ahead, stay positive, and open your heart to the blessings of Umrah. May your journey be safe, easy, and full of reward.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<b>Similar Content: </b><a href=\"https://haqtravels.co.uk/blog/what-is-included-in-an-umrah-package/\"><b>What is Included in an Umrah Package?</b></a></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>', NULL, 1, '2025-05-24 13:55:39', '2025-05-26 16:27:53'),
(16, 'Umrah Gift Ideas for Him and Her: Pro Tips & Guide', 'umrah-gift-ideas-for-him-and-her', '1748276841.jpg', NULL, NULL, 'admin', '<p>\r\n	Umrah is a very special journey in a Muslim&rsquo;s life. It is not just a trip, it is a spiritual journey full of prayer, peace, and closeness to Allah. When someone we love comes back from Umrah, we often want to give them a gift. This is not just to say &ldquo;welcome back,&rdquo; but also to show love, joy, and support for their spiritual journey.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	This article offers a variety of Umrah gift ideas for men and women. you will find meaningful, useful, and beautiful items to choose from. You will discover great ideas here. No matter if you are seeking something spiritual or a special memento from your trip, we have you covered.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<b>Gifting for Umrah Pilgrims</b></h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	Giving gifts is a big part of Islamic culture. It brings people closer together, shows kindness, and spreads love. When someone comes back from Umrah, it&#39;s a great time to give a special gift. This gift should remind them of their spiritual journey.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>The Significance of Giving Gifts After Umrah</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Giving a gift after Umrah isn&rsquo;t just about the item itself. It is about sharing in the happiness of someone who just completed this important act of worship. In Islam, the Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him) encouraged Muslims to give gifts to one another. Gifts help build love and friendship between people.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>What Makes a Perfect Umrah Gift?</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	A perfect Umrah gift doesn&rsquo;t have to be expensive. It should be thoughtful, useful, and meaningful. It can help the person remember their journey or help them in their daily worship. Some gifts are practical, such as prayer items. Others are personal, like jewelry or clothes.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<b>Umrah Gift Ideas for Him</b></h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	When choosing a gift for a man who has returned from Umrah, think about what he might use in his prayers or daily life. Choose something that fits his personality and makes him feel appreciated.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Spiritual &amp; Practical Items</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	<b>A prayer mat</b> is a simple but beautiful gift. Some prayer mats are soft and come with special designs from Makkah or Madinah. You can also find personalized ones with names or messages.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<b>Tasbih</b> (also called misbaha) is another great idea. These are prayer beads used to remember Allah. They come in many colors and sizes and can even be made of wood or gemstones.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<b>An Ihram set</b> can also be a thoughtful gift. While Ihram is worn during Umrah, having a new one shows care and can be saved for future trips.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	You could also give a <b>pocket-sized Qur&rsquo;an</b>. These are easy to carry, especially for someone who travels a lot. Some Qur&rsquo;ans come in leather cases with bookmarks, which makes reading more enjoyable.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Grooming and Personal Care</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	<b>Sunnah perfumes</b>, also called attars, are very popular gifts for men. These are alcohol-free and come in many beautiful scents. They follow the tradition of the Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him), who loved using perfume.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<b>Beard care kits</b> can be useful too. These kits usually have beard oil, combs, and natural products. They help men care for their beards the Sunnah way.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<b>A Miswak</b> is a small stick used for cleaning teeth. It is a Sunnah and a great natural toothbrush. Some Miswak sets come in a case, making them easy to carry around.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Islamic Accessories &amp; Keepsakes</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	If the person likes decoration, a small Kaaba model or a picture of the Prophet&rsquo;s Mosque in Madinah can be a good choice. These make lovely keepsakes.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	You can find Islamic name plaques with Quran verses or names in Arabic calligraphy. These gifts feel personal and can be placed in their home or office.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	A custom kufi or prayer cap is also a good gift. They come in many styles and colors and can be worn during prayers.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<b>Umrah Gift Ideas for Her</b></h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	Women returning from Umrah often value gifts that are lovely and meaningful. Here are some ideas that show care and love.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Elegant &amp; Modest Islamic Apparel</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	A new abaya or jilbab is a lovely gift. These are modest clothes worn by Muslim women and come in many colors and styles. Some have embroidery or simple patterns.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	You can also give a premium hijab gift box. These boxes often include soft, high-quality hijabs in different colors and patterns. It is a thoughtful and practical gift.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Some clothes are made for travel or worship. For example, there are simple dresses for women that work well with Ihram. These are modest and comfortable, great for future Umrah trips.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Islamic Jewelry &amp; Accessories</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Jewelry with Islamic designs can be very special. You can find necklaces with &ldquo;Allah&rdquo; or &ldquo;Ayatul Kursi&rdquo; written on them. These pieces are meaningful and stylish.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Bracelets with Islamic words or names are also great. They can be personalized with the person&rsquo;s name or a special du&rsquo;a.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Beautiful hijab pins with small Arabic letters or symbols like crescents and stars can also be a simple but thoughtful gift.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Spiritual and Self-Care Gifts</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Personalized du&rsquo;a books with the person&rsquo;s name and favorite prayers are meaningful and helpful. These small books help them keep a close connection to Allah.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Scented prayer oils (non-alcoholic) are peaceful and relaxing. Many women like to use them before prayer to feel calm and clean.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	A soft journal for writing reflections after Umrah can help them remember their journey. It gives them a space to write about what they felt, saw, and learned.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<b>Gender-Neutral Umrah Gift Ideas</b></h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	Some gifts can be given to both men and women. These are good if you want something simple that everyone can enjoy.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Travel Essentials for Pilgrims</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Zamzam water is holy water from Makkah. You can buy special bottles with designs or cases to keep it safe. It is a great way to keep a piece of the journey close.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	A Quran speaker is a small device that plays recitations of the Quran. It is helpful for listening while resting, traveling, or during prayer time.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Islamic travel organizers help keep prayer items, documents, and toiletries all in one place. They&rsquo;re practical for anyone who travels often.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Decorative Islamic Home Items</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Islamic wall art with Quranic verses is both spiritual and beautiful. It makes a home feel peaceful and reminds the person of their faith.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Prayer area kits can include a prayer mat, Quran, and small d&eacute;cor for setting up a space to worship at home.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Photos or framed images of Makkah or Madinah are lovely keepsakes. They remind the person of their journey and can be hung in any room.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<b>Personalized Umrah Gift Options</b></h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	Personalized gifts always feel more special. When someone sees their name or a special message on a gift, it becomes more meaningful.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Customization Ideas for Him and Her</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	You can personalize Qur&rsquo;an covers with names or beautiful Islamic designs. Some come in leather or velvet and protect the Qur&rsquo;an while making it look special.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Du&rsquo;a cards with the person&rsquo;s name or messages like &ldquo;Welcome back from Umrah&rdquo; can be a kind touch. They&rsquo;re small but full of love.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Photo albums that include pictures from their Umrah journey are heartfelt. You can add quotes, notes, and space for them to write more about their trip.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<b>Where to Buy Umrah Gifts Online and Locally</b></h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	It is easy to find Umrah gifts both online and in local Islamic stores. Many websites sell beautiful and trusted Islamic gifts.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Trusted Online Islamic Stores</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Some popular online stores are:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Darussalam</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		Etsy (check Islamic gifts)</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\">\r\n		The Islamic Place</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	These sites offer a wide range of gift ideas with quality and halal assurance.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Local Markets in Makkah and Madinah</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	If you are in Saudi Arabia or know someone who is, gifts bought near the holy cities feel even more special. Markets close to the Haram in Makkah and the Prophet&rsquo;s Mosque in Madinah offer unique items. You can find prayer mats, perfumes, and Islamic books there.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<b>Tips for Choosing the Right Umrah Gift</b></h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	Choosing the right gift means thinking about what the person will truly use and enjoy.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Consider Practicality and Sentiment</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Try to choose something that the person can use every day, like a prayer item or Islamic clothing. If it is not useful, it may be forgotten.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Respect Cultural and Religious Sensitivities</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Always choose gifts that respect Islamic values. Avoid anything with pictures or words that may be seen as disrespectful or un-Islamic.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Ensure Halal Compliance and Quality</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	When you buy perfumes, oils, or food items like dates, check for halal certification. Also, check the quality of the gift so it lasts a long time.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<b>Summary</b></h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	Giving a gift to someone who has returned from Umrah is more than just a kind act. It is a way to show love, share happiness, and support their spiritual journey.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	These gifts remind them of their closeness to Allah. They also help them stay on their path with faith and joy. No matter if you pick something personal or practical, big or small, your gift will bring a smile. It will help keep the memories of Umrah alive.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>', NULL, 1, '2025-05-24 13:56:00', '2025-05-26 16:27:21');
INSERT INTO `blogs` (`blogs_id`, `blogs_name`, `blogs_url`, `blogs_image`, `blogs_tag`, `blogs_date`, `blogs_author`, `blogs_details`, `blogs_sort`, `blogs_status`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(17, '4 Star December Umrah Packages: A complete Guide', '4-star-december-umrah-packages-a-complete-guide', '1748274516.jpg', NULL, NULL, 'admin', '<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Planning your Umrah trip in December? You are in for a peaceful and beautiful experience. December is one of the best times to go for Umrah, especially if you want mild weather and more comfort. If you want a nice option that isn&rsquo;t too pricey, consider 4-star December Umrah packages.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	This article will help you learn all about 4-star Umrah packages for December. Discover why December is perfect for Umrah. Find out what the packages include, who should consider them, and how to book one.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<b>Why Choose a 4 Star Umrah Package in December?</b></h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	A 4-star Umrah package in December offers a calm travel experience. You can enjoy comfort without spending too much.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Benefits of Performing Umrah in December</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	December is a peaceful month for Umrah. The weather in Makkah and Madinah is cooler. This makes walking and performing rituals easier. it is not too hot like in summer, so you won&rsquo;t get tired quickly.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Another good thing is that December is not as crowded as Ramadan or Hajj season. This means you can perform your prayers and rituals with more peace and focus.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Advantages of 4 Star Umrah Packages Over 5 Star and Budget Options</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	4 star Umrah packages give you a great balance. They cost less than 5-star packages. Still, they provide good hotels, clean rooms, and helpful services. They are better than budget options. You enjoy more comfort and a better location near the Haram (Holy Mosque).</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	If you want comfort but don&rsquo;t want to spend too much money, then 4 star packages are perfect.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<b>What to Expect in a December 4 Star Umrah Package</b></h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	Knowing what your package includes helps you prepare better and avoid surprises during your journey. You can also learn more about<a href=\"https://haqtravels.co.uk/blog/what-is-included-in-an-umrah-package/\"> <b>what is included in an Umrah package</b></a> for additional clarity.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Hotel Accommodation in Makkah and Madinah</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	With a 4-star package, you often stay in nice hotels near the Haram in Makkah and the Prophet&#39;s Mosque in Madinah. These hotels are clean, safe, and have good service. You may also get daily housekeeping, breakfast, and free Wi-Fi.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Staying close to the mosque saves your energy and time. You don&rsquo;t have to walk long distances, which is especially helpful for older pilgrims and families with children.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Transportation and Transfers</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Most packages include airport pick-up and drop-off. You can get a clean, air-conditioned bus or private car to travel between Makkah and Madinah. Some packages also include local Ziyarat tours to visit historical Islamic sites.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Having transport arranged makes the trip stress-free. You don&rsquo;t have to worry about finding a taxi or getting lost.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Visa Processing and Documentation</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Umrah visa is usually included in the package. The travel agency will help you with the visa application and let you know what documents are needed. Make sure your passport is valid and you have taken any required vaccines.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	In December, the visa process might take a bit longer due to more people applying. So, it is best to book early and give enough time for visa approval.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<b>Price Range and Inclusions: December 2025 4 Star Umrah Deals</b></h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	Knowing the costs and what&rsquo;s in your package can help you budget better.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Typical Pricing for 7, 10, and 14-Day Packages</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Prices for 4-star December Umrah packages vary. They depend on your length of stay and the number of people sharing the room. For example, a 7-day package might cost less, while a 14-day package will cost more.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Sharing a room with more people (quad or triple sharing) will also reduce the price per person. Double sharing is more private but also more expensive.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	These prices are still much cheaper than 5 star packages but more comfortable than 3 star ones.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>What&rsquo;s Included and What&rsquo;s Not</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Usually, a 4 star package includes hotel stay, visa, transport, and sometimes breakfast. Some packages include Ziyarat tours to important places in Makkah and Madinah.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Meals (except breakfast), domestic flights, and personal shopping are usually not included. Always check the full list of what&rsquo;s included before you book.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<b>Who Should Opt for a 4 Star December Umrah Package?</b></h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	Not every traveler has the same needs, here&rsquo;s who can benefit most from these packages.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Ideal for Families and Small Groups</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	If you are traveling with your family or a small group of friends, a 4 star package is a smart choice. It offers comfort and is still affordable. Hotels often offer family rooms. The travel agency can also arrange transport for your group.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Suitable for First-Time Pilgrims</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	If this is your first Umrah, you might need help. You may need guidance on planning, navigating, and performing the rituals correctly.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	You don&rsquo;t have to worry about the small details, so you can focus more on your prayers.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>A Great Choice for Elderly Pilgrims</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Older pilgrims need more comfort and easy access to the Haram. 4-star hotels usually have elevators and wheelchairs. Their staff is trained to assist senior guests. The hotels are also closer to the mosque, so there is less walking.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<b>Best 4 Star Hotels Near Haram &ndash; Makkah &amp; Madinah</b></h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	Good hotels near the Haram make your trip easier and let you focus more on worship.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Top 4-Star Hotels in Makkah</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	There are many good 4 star hotels in Makkah, such as Swissotel Al Maqam and Elaf Ajyad. These hotels are close to the Haram and offer clean rooms, good service, and nice views. Some even have prayer areas inside the hotel.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Staying at a good hotel helps you relax and stay focused during your spiritual journey.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Recommended 4-Star Hotels in Madinah</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	In Madinah, you can stay at hotels like Elaf Taiba or Dallah Taibah. These are just a short walk from the Prophet&rsquo;s Mosque. The rooms are clean and quiet, and the staff is friendly.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	You will find peace in Madinah, and staying near the mosque lets you join the prayers easily.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<b>How to Book the Right December 4 Star Umrah Package</b></h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	Booking the right package ensures a smooth, worry-free trip from start to finish.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Tips for Comparing Umrah Deals Online</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Many travel agencies offer 4 star packages, but not all are the same. Look for clear details like hotel names, distance from Haram, and what&rsquo;s included. Read customer reviews and ratings.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Compare different packages, and don&rsquo;t just choose the cheapest one. Make sure you get good value for your money.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Working with Licensed Travel Agents</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Always book with a licensed and trusted travel agency. Look for agencies that are approved by the Ministry of Hajj and Umrah. These agencies follow rules and give better service.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	You can also ask friends or family for recommendations.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<b>Exclusive Offers on 4 Star December Umrah Packages 2025</b></h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	Special deals and group discounts can save you money and give you better services.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Group Discounts and Family Deals</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Some agencies offer discounts if you book for 4 or more people. You might also find family packages where children get a lower price. Elderly pilgrims may get special attention or added services.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Ask the agency if they have any current deals or offers.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Early Bird Bookings vs Last Minute Deals</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Booking early helps you get better hotel options and smoother visa processing. You may also get early bird discounts.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Last-minute deals can save you money. However, they usually offer fewer options and come with more risk. For peace of mind, book at least 2-3 months before your travel date.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<b>Essential Travel Tips for December Umrah Pilgrims</b></h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	A few simple travel tips can make your pilgrimage more comfortable and stress-free.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>What to Pack for a December Pilgrimage</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	December weather is cooler. Bring a light jacket or sweater, especially for mornings and evenings. Pack comfy walking shoes, prayer clothes, hygiene items, and any needed medicines.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Bring a small bag to carry your essentials when visiting the Haram.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Health and Safety Guidelines</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Stay hydrated, even in cooler weather. Eat light meals and get enough rest. Follow health rules, like wearing a mask in crowded areas if needed.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Make sure you have travel insurance and keep emergency contacts with you.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<b>FAQs About 4 Star Umrah Packages in December</b></h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	Here are some common questions answered to help you feel more confident before you book.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Is December a good month for Umrah?</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Yes, December is a great time to perform Umrah. The weather is cooler, and it is a good time for families and older people to travel.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>How far are 4-star hotels from the Haram?</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Most 4 star hotels are within 5 to 10 minutes walking distance from the Haram. Some are even closer. Always check the hotel&rsquo;s location before booking.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>What&rsquo;s the cancellation policy for Umrah bookings?</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Each travel agency has its own policy. Some allow changes with a small fee, while others may not refund late cancellations. Always read the terms before booking.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<b>Summary</b></h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	A 4 star Umrah package in December gives you the best of both worlds, comfort and value. You stay near the holy sites, enjoy good service, and pay a reasonable price. It is perfect for families, seniors, and first-time pilgrims.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Plan early, pick a trusted travel agent, and make your spiritual journey smooth and meaningful. May your Umrah be accepted and full of blessings.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>', NULL, 1, '2025-05-24 13:56:27', '2025-05-26 15:48:36'),
(18, 'Umrah Visa Fee UK 2025: Cost, Requirements & Application Guide', 'umrah-visa-fee-uk-2025', '1748274808.jpg', NULL, NULL, 'admin', '<p style=\"text-align: center;\">\r\n	Umrah is a special religious journey to Makkah in Saudi Arabia. Unlike Hajj, which happens once a year, Umrah can be done any time. It is not compulsory like Hajj, but it is highly recommended in Islam. Muslims see it as a way to refresh their faith and seek forgiveness.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Growing Popularity of Umrah Among UK Muslims</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	More and more Muslims in the UK are choosing to go for Umrah every year. This is because it is easier now to get a visa, book flights, and find travel packages. Many people travel during school holidays, Ramadan, or winter breaks. They enjoy the cooler weather and have time off work.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<b>Understanding the Umrah Visa Process</b></h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	There are mainly two ways to get a visa for Umrah if you live in the UK. An approved travel agency arranges the traditional Umrah visa. The second one is a tourist visa that also lets you do Umrah. The tourist visa is easy to apply for online and is open to British passport holders.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Umrah Visa Requirements for UK Citizens and Residents</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	To get a visa, you need a passport that is valid for at least six months. You need passport-sized photos. You also need proof of your stay in Saudi Arabia, like hotel bookings. Lastly, bring your return flight tickets. You may also need a certificate for some vaccines like meningitis and COVID-19. If you are not a UK citizen, you will need to show a valid UK residence permit.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<b>Umrah Visa Fee from the UK&nbsp;</b></h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	As of 2025, the average Umrah visa fee for UK residents is around &pound;80 to &pound;150. The exact cost can vary depending on the time of year and which travel agency you use. During busy seasons like Ramadan, prices may be a bit higher because of high demand.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Breakdown of Total Umrah Package Costs</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	When planning your trip, remember that the visa is only part of the cost. You also need to think about flights, hotels, transport, and food. A full Umrah package from the UK usually costs between &pound;1,000 and &pound;2,000. This often includes flights, hotels in Makkah and Madinah, ground transport, and visa fees.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	You can also read more about<a href=\"https://haqtravels.co.uk/blog/how-much-is-umrah-visa-from-uk/\"> <b>how much is Umrah visa from UK</b></a> on our detailed guide that breaks down visa fees, processing options, and real travel costs for 2025.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Additional Charges and Hidden Fees</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Some travel agents may charge service or admin fees, so always ask what&rsquo;s included. If you want your visa faster, there might be an express service fee. Also, medical insurance is sometimes added to the cost. Make sure to get a full breakdown before paying.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<b>How to Apply for an Umrah Visa in the UK</b></h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	First, pick a licensed travel agent that is approved by the Saudi Ministry of Hajj and Umrah. They will guide you through the process. You will need to give them your passport, photos, and other documents. The agent will handle the visa process and book your trip. The whole process usually takes one to two weeks.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Applying Through the Saudi Tourist E-Visa System</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	If you are a British citizen, you can also apply for a tourist visa online. This is quicker and often easier. The tourist visa is valid for one year and lets you visit many places in Saudi Arabia. You can use it to perform Umrah, but not Hajj. Make sure to follow all rules when using this visa for Umrah.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<b>Choosing a Reliable Umrah Travel Agency in the UK</b></h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	Many travel agencies in the UK offer Umrah packages. Cities like London, Birmingham, and Manchester have many options. Choose an agent that is licensed and has good reviews. You can check online or ask friends and family for recommendations.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>What to Look for in a Travel Package</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Check that the package has all you need: flights, hotel, visa, and transport. Check how far the hotel is from the Haram (the Grand Mosque). Some packages include a guide who will help you perform Umrah correctly. Always ask questions and read the contract before you book.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<b>Tips to Save on Umrah Costs from the UK</b></h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	You can save money by traveling during off-peak times. Packages are cheaper outside of Ramadan and school holidays. Group packages often cost less, so consider going with friends or family. Booking early can also help you get better prices.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Avoiding Scams and Overcharging</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Always book with a trusted and licensed agent. Don&rsquo;t pay large amounts upfront without a receipt. Get everything in writing. This includes details about the package and refund policies. You can check the agent&rsquo;s name on the Saudi Hajj Ministry&rsquo;s website.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<b>Common Questions About Umrah Visa Fees</b></h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>How much does an Umrah visa cost in the UK in 2025?</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	The Umrah visa fee in the UK usually ranges from &pound;80 to &pound;150. The price may change depending on the travel agency, the time of year, and whether you use an express service.</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>What is included in an Umrah package from the UK?</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	A full Umrah package usually covers the visa fee, flights, hotel stay, transport in Saudi Arabia, and some meals. Some packages may also include a group guide or mutawwif to assist you during the pilgrimage.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Can I apply for an Umrah visa on my own?</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	If you&#39;re using the Saudi tourist e-visa, yes, you can apply online without an agent. But for a traditional Umrah visa, you need to go through an approved UK-based travel agent.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Is the Umrah visa fee refundable if I cancel my trip?</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	In most cases, the Umrah visa fee is non-refundable, even if your plans change or your visa is rejected. Always ask your travel agent about their refund policy before making payments.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<b>Can I perform Umrah using a Saudi tourist visa?</b></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Yes, British passport holders can use a Saudi tourist visa to perform Umrah. However, you cannot use it for Hajj, and you must follow all rules set by the Saudi authorities.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<b>Conclusion</b></h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	Going for Umrah is a dream for many Muslims in the UK. Understanding the visa process and costs will help you plan better. Make sure to choose a trusted agent, apply early, and budget well. This way, you can focus on the spiritual part of the journey and not worry about last-minute problems.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>', NULL, 1, '2025-05-24 13:56:52', '2025-05-27 13:11:59');
INSERT INTO `blogs` (`blogs_id`, `blogs_name`, `blogs_url`, `blogs_image`, `blogs_tag`, `blogs_date`, `blogs_author`, `blogs_details`, `blogs_sort`, `blogs_status`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(19, 'When Does Umrah Open After Hajj?', 'when-does-umrah-open-after-hajj', '1748455784.jpg', NULL, NULL, 'admin', '<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;\">\r\n	<span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 11pt; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">Umrah usually starts again after the Hajj season ends. In 2025, Umrah will reopen for international pilgrims on June 11, 2025, which is 15 Dhul Hijjah 1447 AH in the Islamic calendar. This date was officially shared by the Ministry of Hajj and Umrah in Saudi Arabia.</span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:18pt;margin-bottom:4pt;\">\r\n	<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-f13ccbc2-7fff-0f9c-c971-09e5a62af750\"><span style=\"font-size: 17pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">Umrah Start Dates After Hajj 2025</span></span></h2>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\">\r\n	<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-f13ccbc2-7fff-0f9c-c971-09e5a62af750\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">Umrah does not begin immediately after Hajj; Saudi authorities set an official start date for international pilgrims each year.</span></span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:14pt;margin-bottom:4pt;\">\r\n	<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-f13ccbc2-7fff-0f9c-c971-09e5a62af750\"><span style=\"font-size: 13pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">Exact Date for Umrah to Resume in 2025</span></span></h3>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;\">\r\n	<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-f13ccbc2-7fff-0f9c-c971-09e5a62af750\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">After the Hajj is completed, Umrah begins again. For 2025, the start date is </span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">June 11, 2025</span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">. This is the day when people from outside Saudi Arabia can begin doing Umrah again.</span></span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:14pt;margin-bottom:4pt;\">\r\n	<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-f13ccbc2-7fff-0f9c-c971-09e5a62af750\"><span style=\"font-size: 13pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">Gregorian vs. Islamic Calendar (June 11 vs. Dhul Hijjah 15)</span></span></h3>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;\">\r\n	<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-f13ccbc2-7fff-0f9c-c971-09e5a62af750\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">In 2025, June 11 matches with 15 Dhul Hijjah 1447 AH.</span></span></p>\r\n<ul style=\"margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px;\">\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\" dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: disc; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre;\">\r\n		<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\">\r\n			<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-f13ccbc2-7fff-0f9c-c971-09e5a62af750\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; text-wrap-mode: wrap;\">The Islamic calendar follows the moon.</span></span></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\" dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: disc; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre;\">\r\n		<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:12pt;\">\r\n			<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-f13ccbc2-7fff-0f9c-c971-09e5a62af750\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; text-wrap-mode: wrap;\">The Gregorian calendar is what most countries use.</span></span></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;\">\r\n	<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-f13ccbc2-7fff-0f9c-c971-09e5a62af750\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">If you&#39;re planning Umrah, it&#39;s good to know both dates, so you don&rsquo;t miss the right time.</span></span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:14pt;margin-bottom:4pt;\">\r\n	<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-f13ccbc2-7fff-0f9c-c971-09e5a62af750\"><span style=\"font-size: 13pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">Announcement by the Ministry of Hajj and Umrah</span></span></h3>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;\">\r\n	<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-f13ccbc2-7fff-0f9c-c971-09e5a62af750\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">The Ministry of Hajj and Umrah in Saudi Arabia is the official source for Umrah dates. In May 2025, they confirmed that Umrah will begin again on June 11, 2025. Always check with trusted travel agents or their official website for updates.</span></span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:18pt;margin-bottom:4pt;\">\r\n	<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-f13ccbc2-7fff-0f9c-c971-09e5a62af750\"><span style=\"font-size: 17pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">Why Is Umrah Paused During Hajj Season?</span></span></h2>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:14pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\">\r\n	<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-f13ccbc2-7fff-0f9c-c971-09e5a62af750\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">Umrah is temporarily paused each year to prioritize the safety and space needed for Hajj pilgrims, due to the large crowds and strict scheduling of Hajj rituals.</span></span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:14pt;margin-bottom:4pt;\">\r\n	<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-f13ccbc2-7fff-0f9c-c971-09e5a62af750\"><span style=\"font-size: 13pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">Logistical Reasons: Managing Hajj Pilgrims</span></span></h3>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;\">\r\n	<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-f13ccbc2-7fff-0f9c-c971-09e5a62af750\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">During Hajj, millions of people come to Makkah. To keep things safe and organized, Umrah is paused. This helps workers and volunteers focus fully on Hajj pilgrims.</span></span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:14pt;margin-bottom:4pt;\">\r\n	<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-f13ccbc2-7fff-0f9c-c971-09e5a62af750\"><span style=\"font-size: 13pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">Visa Restrictions During Dhul Hijjah</span></span></h3>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;\">\r\n	<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-f13ccbc2-7fff-0f9c-c971-09e5a62af750\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">The Saudi government does not issue Umrah visas during the Hajj period. This includes the first 10 days of Dhul Hijjah (the last month of the Islamic year). Only people coming for Hajj can enter Makkah at that time.</span></span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:14pt;margin-bottom:4pt;\">\r\n	<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-f13ccbc2-7fff-0f9c-c971-09e5a62af750\"><span style=\"font-size: 13pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">Differences Between Hajj and Umrah</span></span></h3>\r\n<ul style=\"margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px;\">\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\" dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: disc; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre;\">\r\n		<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\">\r\n			<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-f13ccbc2-7fff-0f9c-c971-09e5a62af750\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; text-wrap-mode: wrap;\">Hajj is a once-in-a-lifetime duty (if you&#39;re able).</span></span></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\" dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: disc; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre;\">\r\n		<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\">\r\n			<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-f13ccbc2-7fff-0f9c-c971-09e5a62af750\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; text-wrap-mode: wrap;\">Umrah is a voluntary act you can do any time, except during Hajj.</span></span></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\" dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: disc; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre;\">\r\n		<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:12pt;\">\r\n			<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-f13ccbc2-7fff-0f9c-c971-09e5a62af750\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; text-wrap-mode: wrap;\">Hajj has fixed dates, but Umrah is open most of the year.</span></span></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:18pt;margin-bottom:4pt;\">\r\n	<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-f13ccbc2-7fff-0f9c-c971-09e5a62af750\"><span style=\"font-size: 17pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">Umrah Visa Reopening Timeline &amp; Application Guide</span></span></h2>\r\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:14pt;margin-bottom:4pt;\">\r\n	<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-f13ccbc2-7fff-0f9c-c971-09e5a62af750\"><span style=\"font-size: 13pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">After Hajj, Saudi Arabia reopens the Umrah visa system with specific timelines, country eligibility, and updated entry rules.</span></span></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:14pt;margin-bottom:4pt;\">\r\n	<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-f13ccbc2-7fff-0f9c-c971-09e5a62af750\"><span style=\"font-size: 13pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">When Can You Apply for an Umrah Visa After Hajj?</span></span></h3>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;\">\r\n	<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-f13ccbc2-7fff-0f9c-c971-09e5a62af750\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">You can usually apply for your Umrah visa about 1&ndash;2 weeks after Hajj ends. In 2025, this means you should be ready to apply by early June if your travel is planned for the reopening on June 11.</span></span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:14pt;margin-bottom:4pt;\">\r\n	<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-f13ccbc2-7fff-0f9c-c971-09e5a62af750\"><span style=\"font-size: 13pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">Countries Eligible for First Batch Post-Hajj</span></span></h3>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;\">\r\n	<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-f13ccbc2-7fff-0f9c-c971-09e5a62af750\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">Some countries may get early access to Umrah visas based on:</span></span></p>\r\n<ul style=\"margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px;\">\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\" dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: disc; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre;\">\r\n		<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\">\r\n			<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-f13ccbc2-7fff-0f9c-c971-09e5a62af750\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; text-wrap-mode: wrap;\">Agreements with Saudi Arabia</span></span></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\" dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: disc; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre;\">\r\n		<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\">\r\n			<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-f13ccbc2-7fff-0f9c-c971-09e5a62af750\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; text-wrap-mode: wrap;\">Past travel record</span></span></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\" dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: disc; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre;\">\r\n		<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:12pt;\">\r\n			<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-f13ccbc2-7fff-0f9c-c971-09e5a62af750\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; text-wrap-mode: wrap;\">Health and vaccination readiness</span></span></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:14pt;margin-bottom:4pt;\">\r\n	<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-f13ccbc2-7fff-0f9c-c971-09e5a62af750\"><span style=\"font-size: 13pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">Expected Processing Times and Requirements</span></span></h3>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;\">\r\n	<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-f13ccbc2-7fff-0f9c-c971-09e5a62af750\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">Here&rsquo;s what you&rsquo;ll usually need:</span></span></p>\r\n<ul style=\"margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px;\">\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\" dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: disc; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre;\">\r\n		<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\">\r\n			<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-f13ccbc2-7fff-0f9c-c971-09e5a62af750\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; text-wrap-mode: wrap;\">A valid passport (at least 6 months left)</span></span></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\" dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: disc; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre;\">\r\n		<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\">\r\n			<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-f13ccbc2-7fff-0f9c-c971-09e5a62af750\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; text-wrap-mode: wrap;\">A visa application through a trusted agent</span></span></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\" dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: disc; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre;\">\r\n		<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\">\r\n			<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-f13ccbc2-7fff-0f9c-c971-09e5a62af750\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; text-wrap-mode: wrap;\">COVID-19 or health documents (if required)</span></span></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\" dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: disc; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre;\">\r\n		<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:12pt;\">\r\n			<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-f13ccbc2-7fff-0f9c-c971-09e5a62af750\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; text-wrap-mode: wrap;\">Hotel bookings and confirmed flights</span></span></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;\">\r\n	<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-f13ccbc2-7fff-0f9c-c971-09e5a62af750\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">Visa processing can take 3 to 7 days, so don&rsquo;t wait too long.</span></span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:18pt;margin-bottom:4pt;\">\r\n	<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-f13ccbc2-7fff-0f9c-c971-09e5a62af750\"><span style=\"font-size: 17pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">Best Time to Perform Umrah After Hajj&nbsp;</span></span></h2>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:14pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\">\r\n	<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-f13ccbc2-7fff-0f9c-c971-09e5a62af750\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">Picking the right time after Hajj can help you avoid crowds, enjoy cooler weather, and have a more peaceful Umrah experience.</span></span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:14pt;margin-bottom:4pt;\">\r\n	<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-f13ccbc2-7fff-0f9c-c971-09e5a62af750\"><span style=\"font-size: 13pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">Why Dhul Hijjah End &amp; Muharram Are Ideal</span></span></h3>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;\">\r\n	<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-f13ccbc2-7fff-0f9c-c971-09e5a62af750\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">The end of Dhul Hijjah and the month of Muharram (first month of the Islamic year) are great times to perform Umrah. Here&rsquo;s why:</span></span></p>\r\n<ul style=\"margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px;\">\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\" dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: disc; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre;\">\r\n		<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\">\r\n			<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-f13ccbc2-7fff-0f9c-c971-09e5a62af750\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; text-wrap-mode: wrap;\">The weather starts to cool down.</span></span></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\" dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: disc; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre;\">\r\n		<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\">\r\n			<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-f13ccbc2-7fff-0f9c-c971-09e5a62af750\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; text-wrap-mode: wrap;\">Most Hajj pilgrims have returned home.</span></span></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\" dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: disc; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre;\">\r\n		<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:12pt;\">\r\n			<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-f13ccbc2-7fff-0f9c-c971-09e5a62af750\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; text-wrap-mode: wrap;\">It&rsquo;s a peaceful time to visit the holy places.</span></span></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;\">\r\n	<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-f13ccbc2-7fff-0f9c-c971-09e5a62af750\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">If you want a calm and meaningful Umrah, these months are perfect.</span></span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:14pt;margin-bottom:4pt;\">\r\n	<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-f13ccbc2-7fff-0f9c-c971-09e5a62af750\"><span style=\"font-size: 13pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">Avoiding Crowds &amp; Booking Early</span></span></h3>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;\">\r\n	<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-f13ccbc2-7fff-0f9c-c971-09e5a62af750\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">To avoid long lines and busy areas:</span></span></p>\r\n<ul style=\"margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px;\">\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\" dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: disc; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre;\">\r\n		<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\">\r\n			<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-f13ccbc2-7fff-0f9c-c971-09e5a62af750\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; text-wrap-mode: wrap;\">Go in the weeks after Dhul Hijjah, not immediately.</span></span></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\" dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: disc; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre;\">\r\n		<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\">\r\n			<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-f13ccbc2-7fff-0f9c-c971-09e5a62af750\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; text-wrap-mode: wrap;\">Book your hotel and flight early ,&nbsp; prices go up quickly!</span></span></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\" dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: disc; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre;\">\r\n		<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:12pt;\">\r\n			<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-f13ccbc2-7fff-0f9c-c971-09e5a62af750\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; text-wrap-mode: wrap;\">Travel in off-peak times like weekdays or mid-month.</span></span></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;\">\r\n	<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-f13ccbc2-7fff-0f9c-c971-09e5a62af750\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">This way, your trip will be smoother and more relaxed.</span></span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:14pt;margin-bottom:4pt;\">\r\n	<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-f13ccbc2-7fff-0f9c-c971-09e5a62af750\"><span style=\"font-size: 13pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">Travel Tips for Elderly and First-Time Pilgrims</span></span></h3>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;\">\r\n	<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-f13ccbc2-7fff-0f9c-c971-09e5a62af750\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">If this is your first Umrah or you&rsquo;re traveling with elders:</span></span></p>\r\n<ul style=\"margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px;\">\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\" dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: disc; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre;\">\r\n		<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\">\r\n			<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-f13ccbc2-7fff-0f9c-c971-09e5a62af750\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; text-wrap-mode: wrap;\">Pick a hotel close to the Haram (less walking).</span></span></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\" dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: disc; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre;\">\r\n		<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\">\r\n			<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-f13ccbc2-7fff-0f9c-c971-09e5a62af750\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; text-wrap-mode: wrap;\">Bring medicines, ID tags, and comfy shoes.</span></span></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\" dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: disc; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre;\">\r\n		<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\">\r\n			<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-f13ccbc2-7fff-0f9c-c971-09e5a62af750\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; text-wrap-mode: wrap;\">Use wheelchair services if needed ,&nbsp; they&rsquo;re available at the mosque.</span></span></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\" dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: disc; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre;\">\r\n		<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:12pt;\">\r\n			<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-f13ccbc2-7fff-0f9c-c971-09e5a62af750\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; text-wrap-mode: wrap;\">Book with an agent who understands senior needs.</span></span></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:18pt;margin-bottom:4pt;\">\r\n	<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-f13ccbc2-7fff-0f9c-c971-09e5a62af750\"><span style=\"font-size: 17pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ)</span></span></h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:14pt;margin-bottom:4pt;\">\r\n	<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-f13ccbc2-7fff-0f9c-c971-09e5a62af750\"><span style=\"font-size: 13pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">How long after Hajj does Umrah reopen?</span></span></h3>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;\">\r\n	<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-f13ccbc2-7fff-0f9c-c971-09e5a62af750\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">Umrah usually reopens about 5 to 7 days after Hajj ends. This short break helps Saudi authorities handle Hajj pilgrims leaving and get ready for Umrah visitors arriving. In 2025, Umrah will resume on June 11.</span></span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:14pt;margin-bottom:4pt;\">\r\n	<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-f13ccbc2-7fff-0f9c-c971-09e5a62af750\"><span style=\"font-size: 13pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">Can I perform Umrah during Hajj?</span></span></h3>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;\">\r\n	<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-f13ccbc2-7fff-0f9c-c971-09e5a62af750\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">No, Umrah is suspended during the Hajj season. This pause makes sure that all resources and space in Makkah are saved just for Hajj pilgrims. Umrah resumes after the main Hajj rituals are completed.</span></span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:14pt;margin-bottom:4pt;\">\r\n	<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-f13ccbc2-7fff-0f9c-c971-09e5a62af750\"><span style=\"font-size: 13pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">What is the first date Umrah opens in 2025?</span></span></h3>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;\">\r\n	<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-f13ccbc2-7fff-0f9c-c971-09e5a62af750\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">The official Umrah reopening date for international pilgrims in 2025 is June 11, which is 15 Dhul Hijjah 1447 AH. This date was confirmed by the Ministry of Hajj and Umrah in Saudi Arabia.</span></span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:14pt;margin-bottom:4pt;\">\r\n	<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-f13ccbc2-7fff-0f9c-c971-09e5a62af750\"><span style=\"font-size: 13pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">Do I need a new visa if I perform Hajj?</span></span></h3>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;\">\r\n	<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-f13ccbc2-7fff-0f9c-c971-09e5a62af750\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">Yes, a separate Umrah visa is required even if you just completed Hajj. Hajj and Umrah are two distinct pilgrimages. They have different visa requirements. You cannot perform both on the same visa.</span></span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:14pt;margin-bottom:4pt;\">\r\n	<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-f13ccbc2-7fff-0f9c-c971-09e5a62af750\"><span style=\"font-size: 13pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">Is Umrah available to all nationalities immediately after Hajj?</span></span></h3>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;\">\r\n	<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-f13ccbc2-7fff-0f9c-c971-09e5a62af750\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">Not always. Umrah is reopening for most countries, but some nationalities might face delays. This can happen due to Saudi regulations, health guidelines, or visa agreements. Check with your local travel agency or the Ministry&rsquo;s updates.</span></span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:18pt;margin-bottom:4pt;\">\r\n	<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-f13ccbc2-7fff-0f9c-c971-09e5a62af750\"><span style=\"font-size: 17pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">Final Tips for Planning Your Post-Hajj Umrah</span></span></h2>\r\n<ul style=\"margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px;\">\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\" dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: disc; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre;\">\r\n		<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\">\r\n			<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-f13ccbc2-7fff-0f9c-c971-09e5a62af750\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; text-wrap-mode: wrap;\">Book flights and hotels early Availability goes fast after Hajj. The earlier you book, the better the price.</span></span></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\" dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: disc; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre;\">\r\n		<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\">\r\n			<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-f13ccbc2-7fff-0f9c-c971-09e5a62af750\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; text-wrap-mode: wrap;\">Get health certificates and vaccinations. Ensure your COVID-19, meningitis, and other required vaccines are current.</span></span></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\" dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: disc; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre;\">\r\n		<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\">\r\n			<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-f13ccbc2-7fff-0f9c-c971-09e5a62af750\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; text-wrap-mode: wrap;\">Choose trusted travel agencies like Haq Travels. They&rsquo;ll manage your visa, flights, and hotel together.</span></span></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\" dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: disc; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre;\">\r\n		<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:12pt;\">\r\n			<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-f13ccbc2-7fff-0f9c-c971-09e5a62af750\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; text-wrap-mode: wrap;\">Check the Ministry of Hajj and Umrah announcements. Always visit the official website for the latest rules and dates.</span></span></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>', NULL, 1, '2025-05-28 18:09:44', '2025-05-28 18:09:44');
